Author: Cristina de-la-Rosa-Gay [aut, cre], Daniel Fernández [ctb]
Maintainer: Cristina de-la-Rosa-Gay <mdelarosa@uoc.edu>
Description: oralR offers support for dental notation handling, including 
	detection, parsing, and conversion between FDI, Universal and 
	Alphanumeric systems, as well as data tidying helpers for clinical
	datasets. It also provides tools for analyzing clinical, periodontal and orthodontic
	data, including functions for computing DMFT/DEF, BOP, PCR, PI, PSI and
	ICON indices. Additional utilities are included for descriptive
	statistics and prevalence estimation.
